I Cant Do Anything Right

My Dreams always fade,

The pain never runs away,

Always lying on the ground,

Cause I got pushed down and couldnt get back up.

 

It always seems like I'm Screwing up,

The smallest mistakes mess up my entire life,

I cant do anything right.

 

Every time I run away,

I always come back,

Cause I have chain holding me back,

Everything is always wrong.

 

I am so sick of the same people,

Their fake smiles,

Their stupid lies,

Their all the same.

 

They always lie to my face,

They stab me in the back,

They Kick me when I'm down,

They make me wear a frown.

 

I cant do anything right,

Smallest mistakes screw my life all up,

No one around to help,

I'm glued to the ground.

By: Jessie

Welcome to my World

You dont know the first thing about me,

To be kicked when you're down,

And there is no one there to help you,

Get up off the ground.

 

You dont know whats it like,

To be stabbed in the back,

By your best friend,

For your entire life.

 

They lied right to my face,

And behind my back,

Saying they were my friends,

But that was a lie.

 

I lock the door, Turn my stereo up, So no one hears my scream.

They say are you alright,

I tell them I'm okay,

But when I look in the mirror,

I just wanna run away.

 

Its not fair to be kicked when your down,

Its not fair to be hated,

When you did nothin wrong!

 

You tried to be their friends,

But they always talked smack,

They ditched you when you walkin,

Then stabbed you in the back.

 

I'm not gonna be okay,

The worries never run away,

So I just hold my head high,

And say that I'm Okay.

 

Welcome to my World,

Where the pain never runs away,

Dreams always fade,

To feel like I cant do anything right.
